<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="id0db4645a-3a70-11f1-a648-bee82ed8a795" identifier="/us/usc/t20/s1704"><num value="1704">§ 1704.</num><heading> Balance not required</heading><content>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">The failure of an educational agency to attain a balance, on the basis of race, color, sex, or national origin, of students among its schools shall not constitute a denial of equal educational opportunity, or equal protection of the laws.</p>
</content><sourceCredit id="id0db4645b-3a70-11f1-a648-bee82ed8a795">(<ref href="/us/pl/93/380/tII/s205">Pub. L. 93–380, title II, § 205</ref>, <date date="1974-08-21">Aug. 21, 1974</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/88/515">88 Stat. 515</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
<notes type="uscNote" id="id0db4645c-3a70-11f1-a648-bee82ed8a795">
<note style="-uslm-lc:I74" role="crossHeading" topic="statutoryNotes" id="id0db4645d-3a70-11f1-a648-bee82ed8a795"><heading class="centered"><b>Statutory Notes and Related Subsidiaries</b></heading></note>
<note style="-uslm-lc:I74" topic="effectiveDate" id="id0db4645e-3a70-11f1-a648-bee82ed8a795"><heading class="centered smallCaps">Effective Date</heading><p style="-uslm-lc:I21" class="indent0">Section effective on and after sixtieth day after <date date="1974-08-21">Aug. 21, 1974</date>, see <ref href="/us/pl/93/380/s2/c">section 2(c) of Pub. L. 93–380</ref>, set out as a note under <ref href="/us/usc/t20/s1221–1">section 1221–1 of this title</ref>.</p>
</note>
</notes>
